  "extractionRules": [
    "Distinguish allegations, arguments, findings, holdings, and final outcomes. Do not treat a party submission as a court finding.",
    "Prefer precise statutory section nodes over broad statute nodes when a section is mentioned.",
    "Capture police and prosecution lapses only when the court discusses them, not merely because a party alleges them.",
    "For every outcome edge, capture the reason or evidence relationship that the court relied on when available.",
    "Capture precedents separately from the judgment being processed and mark whether they were followed, distinguished, or disapproved when stated.",
    "For judgment workspaces, use only ontology-approved node and edge types in the approved graph. Quarantine any proposed new type for reviewer action.",
    "Capture authority status and later treatment only when stated by the judgment, a recognized citation source, or a reviewed legal update.",
    "Capture legal regime using the offence or incident date when available. Do not assume BNS/BNSS/BSA applicability merely because the judgment was delivered after transition.",
    "Use investigation_lapse nodes only for legally material lapses such as delay, non-compliance, missing witnesses, chain-of-custody gaps, and forensic defects.",
    "High-risk causal edges such as outcome_caused_by, supports_acquittal, lapse_caused_doubt, and non_compliance_with require a quoted source span before promotion to reviewed status.",
    "Mark victim, minor, sexual-offence, sealed-record, and medical-identity details with sensitive_data_marker nodes when present.",
    "When a judgment contains both conviction and acquittal for different accused or charges, create separate outcome nodes or edges for each party/charge.",
    "For district/trial-court judgments, capture witness credibility, evidence gaps, bail reasoning, sentencing, and procedural defects only when the court states them.",
    "Do not infer guilt, innocence, police misconduct, witness credibility, or officer-facing lessons beyond the judgment text and reviewer-approved guidance."
  ],
  "answerUseGuidance": [
    "Use reviewed wiki articles for doctrine and recurring lessons.",
    "Use graph paths for relationships between issues, evidence, lapses, outcomes, courts, and statutes.",
    "Use raw chunks from the vector and lexical indexes for every answer that makes a source-specific claim.",
    "Expose confidence and review status when graph or wiki information is not fully reviewed.",
    "Include a corpus validity card for pattern or success-rate answers.",
    "Suppress or redact sensitive identities unless the user role is authorized and the access is audited."
  ],
